00:00:25,353 --> 00:00:27,020
"To perfect
is to change often."

4
00:00:27,021 --> 00:00:28,857
You know your Churchill.

5
00:00:28,922 --> 00:00:30,438
Inscribed on the
watch you gave me

6
00:00:30,439 --> 00:00:32,232
- when I left for Glendon Hill.
- Was it?

7
00:00:32,234 --> 00:00:34,818
- Nancy arranges all the gifts.
- She knows you well.

8
00:00:34,819 --> 00:00:37,778
- As much as I'm enjoying this little...
- I got you two more votes.

9
00:00:37,780 --> 00:00:40,823
Partridge and Krauss.

10
00:00:40,824 --> 00:00:43,282
Is this Raymond's way
of extending an olive branch?

11
00:00:43,283 --> 00:00:47,411
- It's a start.
- Two votes is a twig. It's not a branch.

12
00:00:47,412 --> 00:00:51,288
- Which is why I'm here.
- Well, the vote is at 5:00.

13
00:00:51,289 --> 00:00:54,792
- We have less than three hours.
- Two hours and 49 minutes.

14
00:00:54,793 --> 00:00:57,836
- We have made more happen in less.
- Is that the watch?

15
00:00:57,837 --> 00:01:03,091
- No, it's nicer. - So why did Raymond
have a change of heart?

16
00:01:03,092 --> 00:01:05,342
If the government grinds
to a halt, that benefits no one.

17
00:01:05,343 --> 00:01:09,345
We want the president focused on China,
not distracted by furloughs and protests.

18
00:01:09,346 --> 00:01:12,180
You take direction
from Jacqueline.

19
00:01:12,181 --> 00:01:13,681
She's not gonna
like that very much.

20
00:01:13,683 --> 00:01:15,725
- Bossing you around?
- Having me around.

21
00:01:15,726 --> 00:01:18,602
I don't blame her.

22
00:01:18,603 --> 00:01:20,645
Ashleigh will start
the interview with questions

23
00:01:20,646 --> 00:01:23,397
about how you and your husband
met, your early marriage.

24
00:01:23,398 --> 00:01:25,942
- Fine.
- Then she'll move on to more specific

25
00:01:25,943 --> 00:01:31,737
- questions about your recent transition.
- All right.

26
00:01:31,738 --> 00:01:34,448
She's gonna ask about you
having no children.

27
00:01:34,449 --> 00:01:36,408
I thought we agreed
to take that off the table.

28
00:01:36,409 --> 00:01:37,659
We did, but they insisted.

29
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:39,618
Now, I can speak
to Ashleigh directly and...

30
00:01:39,619 --> 00:01:41,620
No, no. It's fine. I've been
asked the question before.

31
00:01:41,621 --> 00:01:43,622
- I know how to answer it.
- It'll be quick and painless.

32
00:01:43,623 --> 00:01:46,874
I'll confirm that with Ashleigh
when she gets here.

33
00:01:46,875 --> 00:01:49,543
- I like it.
- Maybe something less neutral.

34
00:01:49,544 --> 00:01:53,672
I'm sure you'll look good in
whatever you choose. I'll be downstairs.

35
00:01:57,175 --> 00:02:00,176
Disori owes you for the
overpass funding you secured.

36
00:02:00,177 --> 00:02:02,053
- Yes, he does.
- I'll call him.

37
00:02:02,054 --> 00:02:03,846
- Where's Doug?
- He's doing the rounds.

38
00:02:03,847 --> 00:02:06,347
Making sure our
hard ones stay hard.

39
00:02:06,348 --> 00:02:09,100
Birch and Womack are doing the same.
But we're still 15 short.

40
00:02:09,101 --> 00:02:11,435
I've got relationships
with most of these folks.

41
00:02:11,436 --> 00:02:14,771
Money's not enough.
I already tried the D-trip route.

42
00:02:14,772 --> 00:02:16,647
Retirement age is
the main sticking point?

43
00:02:16,648 --> 00:02:19,275
- Old people vote.
- I'll target the AARP.

44
00:02:19,276 --> 00:02:21,943
- That'll take most of the heat off.
- We're wasting time.

45
00:02:21,944 --> 00:02:24,695
- I gotta get to work.
- Take Remy with you.

46
00:02:24,696 --> 00:02:26,113
Shouldn't we divide and conquer?

47
00:02:26,114 --> 00:02:28,782
It's harder to say no
twice than once.

48
00:02:28,783 --> 00:02:29,991
I'll stay out of your way.

49
00:02:29,992 --> 00:02:31,492
Like you did
on the watershed act?

50
00:02:31,493 --> 00:02:32,993
We're on the same
side of the fence.

51
00:02:32,994 --> 00:02:34,535
You're late to the party.

52
00:02:34,536 --> 00:02:36,537
Think of Remy as the guy
who shows up

53
00:02:36,538 --> 00:02:39,166
with a six-pack after
the liquor stores close.

54
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:41,834
- Who's on your plate?
- Donald Blythe.

55
00:02:41,835 --> 00:02:44,085
Do you really think that's
the best use of your time?

56
00:02:44,086 --> 00:02:46,045
If I can get him
to turn his people.

57
00:02:46,046 --> 00:02:47,880
A lot of eggs
to put in one basket.

58
00:02:47,881 --> 00:02:49,299
We only have one basket.

59
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:52,008
Jacqueline,
may I use your office,

60
00:02:52,009 --> 00:02:55,846
- for old time's sake? - I serve at the
pleasure of the vice president.

61
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,350
Two hours and 17 minutes.

62
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:08,313
Normally all I need to sway
Donald Blythe is patience and time,

63
00:03:08,314 --> 00:03:10,648
neither of which
I have right now.

64
00:03:10,649 --> 00:03:13,693
Tick tock.

