a direction I knew would make you unhappy.

83
00:05:42,725 --> 00:05:45,268
- I saw no reason to frustrate...
- You eviscerated the unions.

84
00:05:45,269 --> 00:05:48,146
- You federalized performance standards.
- If we hadn't done that,

85
00:05:48,147 --> 00:05:49,814
the bill would've
been dead in the water.

86
00:05:49,815 --> 00:05:51,190
Now you want to cut
the pathetic level

87
00:05:51,191 --> 00:05:52,732
of funding you
did manage to pass.

88
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:56,026
Isn't some funding better
than none?

89
00:05:56,027 --> 00:05:59,154
A flatline will send a louder
message than life support.

90
00:05:59,155 --> 00:06:04,158
Look, I'm impressed with the
little coalition you've cobbled together,

91
00:06:04,159 --> 00:06:08,078
- but we...
- Not so little. Twenty-eight votes.

92
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:11,998
- And you need them all.
- Well, really only half.

93
00:06:11,999 --> 00:06:16,168
- Half of zero is still zero.
- I had to pull every trick in the book

94
00:06:16,169 --> 00:06:18,669
to get entitlement through
the Senate. If it fails in the House,

95
00:06:18,671 --> 00:06:21,088
we don't get a round two.
This is a one-time deal.

96
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:24,632
It should never have passed
the Senate to begin with.

97
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:28,636
Can we start over?
May I offer you an apology?

98
00:06:28,637 --> 00:06:31,762
Deaf ears, Frank.

99
00:06:31,763 --> 00:06:36,100
I withdrew myself from the education
fight and that is my cross to bear.

100
00:06:36,101 --> 00:06:38,893
But I will be damned if I will
make the same mistake twice.

101
00:06:38,894 --> 00:06:43,440
This sort of stubbornness
makes you no better than the tea party.

102
00:06:45,191 --> 00:06:49,152
- Except for the fact...
- that we happen to be right.

103
00:06:49,153 --> 00:06:53,070
Just a few more minutes, Donald.
You haven't even had your seltzer yet.

104
00:06:53,071 --> 00:06:55,990
They have seven other data centers
spread across the Northeast.

105
00:06:55,991 --> 00:06:58,451
- Those aren't good odds.
- Well, if we can access one,

106
00:06:58,452 --> 00:07:00,910
I should be able to talk to the
other seven. They all look like that.

107
00:07:00,911 --> 00:07:03,578
- Fort Knox wrapped in a nuclear bunker.
- How do we get in?

108
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:06,415
Well, we don't. You do.

109
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:10,626
What...? How?
What's my reason?

110
00:07:10,627 --> 00:07:14,087
You're writing a story on cyberterrorism.
It's free publicity.

111
00:07:14,088 --> 00:07:16,214
- If they're so secure...
- They give tours all the time.

112
00:07:16,215 --> 00:07:19,175
- Mostly to prospective clients.
- Then why haven't you done it yourself?

113
00:07:19,176 --> 00:07:22,219
Because I run a white hat firm.

114
00:07:22,220 --> 00:07:25,557
And if I were to show up in the tour logs
before a breach, it would raise alarms.

115
00:07:28,517 --> 00:07:31,352
OK. Once I'm in?

116
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:34,854
These are what
servers look like.

117
00:07:34,855 --> 00:07:37,189
If you can get inside one of
these cages, you will have this.

118
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:41,859
You slide it into
the server. VoilÃ .

119
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:44,361
- It's that simple?
- Yeah. Well, your part, not mine.

120
00:07:44,362 --> 00:07:47,322
- Code's extremely complex.
- How do I do it without them noticing?

121
00:07:47,323 --> 00:07:51,868
You get good at anything.
Practice makes perfect.

122
00:08:07,088 --> 00:08:09,090
We've got a problem.

123
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:18,388
Everyone, stop what you're doing, head
into the nearest office and shut the door.

124
00:08:18,389 --> 00:08:21,475
You, stay exactly where you are.

125
00:08:28,272 --> 00:08:30,313
Retirement age is a done deal.

126
00:08:30,314 --> 00:08:32,482
I might be able to
redistribute some appropriations...

127
00:08:32,483 --> 00:08:36,651
That's not what I'm after. You can't fix
a wrecked car with new hubcaps.

128
00:08:36,652 --> 00:08:39,737
How about a sister bill?
One that focuses entirely on education.

129
00:08:39,738 --> 00:08:42,656
My coalition is fighting
for the integrity of the party.

130
00:08:42,657 --> 00:08:44,657
We're not just
focused on education...

131
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:46,617
I'm sorry, Donald.
Excuse me.

132
00:08:46,618 --> 00:08:49,912
Nancy, I said no interrup...

133
00:08:49,914 --> 00:08:51,705
When?

134
00:08:51,706 --> 00:08:54,541
But the vote is in
less than an hour. I...

135
00:08:54,542 --> 00:09:00,169
I don't care what protocol... Quarantine.
There's white powder in the mail.

136
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:03,672
- We're locked in?
- Sir! Close the door now!

137
00:09:03,673 --> 00:09:07,051
- Look, I have to...
- Now, sir! Please!

138
00:09:08,553 --> 00:09:12,430
- I should call my wife.
- And I should call Claire.

139
00:09:12,431 --> 00:09:16,349
- Should I tell Connor?
<i>- No. It's better the press doesn't know.</i>

140
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:18,851
Field tests should come in before the vote.
Soon as the tally's in,

141
00:09:18,852 --> 00:09:21,061
- I'll come home.
<i>- How's it looking?</i>

142
00:09:21,062 --> 00:09:23,439
Shaky. We may lose this one.

143
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,982
That could make
for a tough interview.

144
00:09:25,983 --> 00:09:28,109
<i>Well, I didn't want</i>
<i>to do it in the first place.</i>

145
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,901
Well, we're committed now.

146
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:32,571
<i>I better get</i>
<i>back to the holy crusader.</i>

147
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,863
Let me know as soon
as the tests have cleared.

148
00:09:34,864 --> 00:09:36,532
If we're lucky,
it'll be anthrax.

149
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,242
I won't live long enough
to see the bill fail.

150
00:09:38,243 --> 00:09:41,244
- Don't say that.
<i>- We're gonna be fine.</i>

151
00:09:41,245 --> 00:09:43,621
<i>How many of these quarantines</i>
<i>we been through?</i>

152
00:09:43,622 --> 00:09:46,372
- I've lost count.
- <i> Wish me luck with Donald.</i>

153
00:09:46,373 --> 00:09:48,833
Heels crossed.

154
00:09:48,834 --> 00:09:51,294
- It's ripping the caucus apart.
- Of course.

155
00:09:51,295 --> 00:09:54,045
We took a united stand
on our version of the bill.

156
00:09:54,046 --> 00:09:57,632
- Some of us have to stay on our feet.
- This is about party unity.

157
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:01,384
- It's about abandoning our base.
- No. That's what the freeze is.

158
00:10:01,385 --> 00:10:03,261
Our base doesn't benefit
from sword rattling.

159
00:10:03,262 --> 00:10:05,262
It gets left
bleeding on the field.

160
00:10:05,263 --> 00:10:08,182
My district has the third largest number
of seniors in the country.

161
00:10:08,183 --> 00:10:11,809
If we raise the age
of retirement, the AARP will raise hell.

162
00:10:11,810 --> 00:10:14,353
I spoke with the president
of the AARP this morning.

163
00:10:14,354 --> 00:10:17,271
They'll be receiving
a 45 million dollar endowment next week.

164
00:10:17,272 --> 00:10:19,273
Voters will still revolt.

165
00:10:19,274 --> 00:10:21,359
The midterms are gonna be ugly.

166
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,360
Many, and I can speak
for myself...

167
00:10:23,361 --> 00:10:26,655
The choice is between immediate
discontinuation of services

168
00:10:26,656 --> 00:10:29,114
and an age bump
five years from now.

169
00:10:29,115 --> 00:10:33,284
You're comparing theoretical
discomfort to imminent pain.

170
00:10:33,285 --> 00:10:35,911
I just feel like we're losing
touch with our core values.

171
00:10:35,912 --> 00:10:38,288
The education bill
was a good example.

172
00:10:38,289 --> 00:10:40,666
We all followed Frank's lead,
hoping it would buy us

173
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:44,461
- traction with the Republicans.
- Would you excuse me? Just one moment.

174
00:10:48,422 --> 00:10:50,756
- Does the press know?
- Not yet.

175
00:10:50,757 --> 00:10:52,675
Can you keep in touch with him?

176
00:10:52,676 --> 00:10:55,968
I need to pummel our lunch
guests into submission.

177
00:10:55,969 --> 00:10:59,304
You got 'em close,
but relax. Listen more.

178
00:10:59,305 --> 00:11:02,848
They want their hands held,
not someone in their face.

179
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:05,934
I know how to whip votes.

180
00:11:05,935 --> 00:11:08,062
Best caviar in DC,
ladies and gentlemen.

181
00:11:08,063 --> 00:11:10,146
- We can't let you pay for that.
- Then don't eat it.

182
00:11:10,147 --> 00:11:13,691
But if you do,
I won't tell anyone.

183
00:11:13,692 --> 00:11:16,318
You were saying
about the education bill...

184
00:11:29,246 --> 00:11:34,708
No, Marjory, honey. Remember,
we just talked about it.

185
00:11:34,709 --> 00:11:36,167
I was telling you...

186
00:11:37,126 --> 00:11:39,421
Right. Nothing to worry about.

187
00:11:41,046 --> 00:11:43,172
If you have any questions,
ask Molly.

188
00:11:43,173 --> 00:11:45,299
She knows what's going on.

189
00:11:47,134 --> 00:11:50,303
I will call as soon
as I know anything.

190
00:11:52,222 --> 00:11:54,140
I love you.

191
00:11:57,059 --> 00:11:58,893
How's Marjory?

192
00:12:04,356 --> 00:12:08,526
- She's OK.
- Long call.

193
00:12:08,527 --> 00:12:13,405
You know, she... gets emotional.

194
00:12:13,406 --> 00:12:16,197
Molly took a semester off
to be at home.

195
00:12:16,198 --> 00:12:18,324
I told her she needs
to head back in the spring.

196
00:12:18,325 --> 00:12:21,827
I don't want her mother
dragging her down.

197
00:12:21,828 --> 00:12:25,414
- Must be hard on you.
- Harder on the girls, I think.

198
00:12:25,415 --> 00:12:29,292
- Is she lucid?
- About half the time.

199
00:12:29,293 --> 00:12:33,587
Just enough to be aware
of how quickly she's going.

200
00:12:33,588 --> 00:12:35,715
It's awful.

201
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:46,012
I feel terrible saying it, but part of me
is looking forward to her not being lucid.

202
00:12:46,013 --> 00:12:49,391
At least then she won't
realize what's happening.

203
00:12:51,101 --> 00:12:53,268
I should have thought
of this before.

204
00:12:53,269 --> 00:12:56,105
Appeal to the heart,
not the brain.

205
00:12:57,648 --> 00:12:59,690
Forgive my ignorance, but...

206
00:12:59,691 --> 00:13:03,485
...has there been any
progress with research?

207
00:13:03,486 --> 00:13:09,406
Some. Genetic testing,
vascular manipulation. But it's slow.

208
00:13:09,407 --> 00:13:12,451
They won't come up with
anything in time for Marjory.

209
00:13:12,452 --> 00:13:16,495
We're focusing on quality of life.
Look, I know you have work to do, so...

210
00:13:16,497 --> 00:13:18,789
I'm no longer the whip.
That's Jacqueline's job.

211
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:21,458
I just agreed to meet with you
because we have a history.

212
00:13:21,459 --> 00:13:23,459
She would be tougher
to say no to.

213
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:25,585
But it still
would've been a "no."

214
00:13:25,586 --> 00:13:29,963
- Yes.
- I admire your convictions, Donald.

215
00:13:29,964 --> 00:13:31,923
You're a rare breed nowadays.

216
00:13:31,924 --> 00:13:34,550
It didn't sound that way when
you were comparing us to the tea party.

217
00:13:34,551 --> 00:13:39,137
I was being unfair. You're not
a reactionary. You're a progressive.

218
00:13:39,138 --> 00:13:44,351
- I see where this is going.
- How do you mean?

219
00:13:44,352 --> 00:13:49,521
When you've been in the
wasteland as long as I have,
you become immune to flattery.

220
00:13:49,522 --> 00:13:52,731
I know you think I'm
fundamentally deceptive,

221
00:13:52,732 --> 00:13:55,442
but I am capable
of a genuine compliment.

222
00:13:55,443 --> 00:13:58,736
Then I will take it as one,
but it won't soften my resolve.

223
00:13:58,737 --> 00:14:02,782
If it did, you wouldn't deserve
the compliment in the first place.

224
00:14:02,783 --> 00:14:05,367
If you vote no,
I won't hold it against you.

225
00:14:05,368 --> 00:14:08,285
We are all in this together
through the midterms.

226
00:14:08,286 --> 00:14:14,415
But, if you stick with me,
we can show both the Republicans

